    "In volatile trading environments like the marked period in Fig. 12, the MACD can generate misleading signals, leading to a series of unprofitable trades.",
    "The standard signal thresholds of MACD may not be adaptable enough for all market conditions, particularly in volatile settings.",
    "This limitation underscores the need for a more dynamic approach, possibly integrating adaptive thresholds that account for the prevailing market volatility.Limitation 3: High turnover rate results in high transaction fee.",
